{{more footnotes|date=February 2017|blp=yes}} {{refimprove|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox writer |name = Bhawani Bhikshu |native_name = Bhawani Prasad Gupta |birth_name = Nohar Ram Gupta |birth_place = [[Taulihawa]], [[Kapilvastu district]], [[Nepal]] |birth_date = 1966 B.S., Jestha 21 |death_date = 2038 B.S., Baisakh 4 |death_place = [[Kathmandu, Nepal]] |occupation = Story writer, novel writer, academic |known_for = Female-centered stories and ethnic Terai stories in [[Nepali language]] |notable_works = ''Aagat'', ''Pipe no.2'', ''Gunakeshari'', ''Maiyasaheb'' |awards = [[Madan Puraskar]] 2032 B.S., [[Sajha Purashkar]] 2032 B.S., Tribhuwan Pragya Puraskar 2036 B.S. |nationality = [[Nepal]]i |ethnicity = [[Madhesi Nepalese]] }} '''Bhawani Bhikshu''' ({{lang-ne|[[:ne: भवानी भिक्षु| भवानी भिक्षु]]}}) is a Nepali literary figure. His real name was Bhawani Prasad Gupta. At the age of 4 years, he was at the mouth of the death, suffering from Bifar [Smallpox]. It is also said that his life was saved due to divine and the power of Goddess Durga. His father Indra Prasad Gupta was a landseller. That's why there was no scarcity of basic needs. He completed his school life in India because of the scarcity of schools in Nepal. Although he was unable to complete his higher studies, he studied independently. He was interested in writing.
