{{Infobox writer | name = Bhuwan Thapaliya | image = | caption = | birth_date = 6 May 1976 | birth_place = [[Kathmandu]], Nepal | residence = [[Kathmandu]], Nepal | nationality = Nepalese | occupation = Poet, Editor, Writer, Economist | genre = [[English poetry]] | alma mater = | website = }}
'''Bhuwan Thapaliya''' ({{lang-ne|भूवन थपलिया}}) is a [[Nepali people|Nepali]] poet and economist from [[Kathmandu]], [[Nepal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=BHUWAN THAPALIYA|url=http://www.cyberwit.net/authors/bhuwan-thapaliya|website=Cyberwit.net|accessdate=27 July 2014}}</ref> His recent book is Safa Tempo: Poems New and Selected.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Thapaliya|first1=Bhuwan|title=Safa tempo : poems new and selected|date=2011|publisher=Nirala Publications|location=New Delhi|isbn=9788182500365|edition=1st|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JnYptwAACAAJ&dq=Safa+Tempo:+Poems+New+and+Selected&hl=en&sa=X&ei=m3fVU_X-N4yUyATKhYHgBQ&ved=0CBsQ6AEwAA|accessdate=27 July 2014}}</ref>
==Life and career==
Thapaliya has published four poetry collections so far. He works as an economist and lives in Kathmandu. His poetry has been published in The New Pleiades Anthology of Poetry and Tonight: An Anthology of World Love Poetry, in literary journals such as Urhalpool, MahMag, Kritya, FOLLY, The Vallance Review, Nuvein Magazine, Foundling Review, Poetry Life and Times, Poets Against the War, Voices in Wartime and Taj Mahal Review.
== Published works ==
* Our Nepal, Our Pride (Cyberwit.net) * Safa Tempo: Poems New and Selected *
