{{other uses|Jamaican (disambiguation)}} {{Use Jamaican English|date=March 2012}} {{Infobox ethnic group |flag = [[File:Flag of Jamaica.svg|border|300px]] |flag_caption = [[Flag of Jamaica|National Flag of Jamaica]] |total = {{circa}} '''4.4 million''' |popplace = Jamaica &nbsp; {{UN_Population|Jamaica}}{{UN_Population|ref}} |region1 = United States |pop1 = 800,000+ |ref1 = <ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=ACS_13_1YR_B04003&prodType=table Results &nbsp;] American Fact Finder (US Census Bureau)</ref> |region3 = Canada |pop3 = 300,000+ |ref3 = <ref name="CanadaCensus2011">[http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/nhs-enm/2011/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=PR&Code1=01&Data=Count&SearchText=canada&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&A1=All&B1=All&Custom=&TABID=1 NHS Profile, Canada, 2011], Statistics Canada. Retrieved December 2nd, 2013</ref><ref name=jamaicans>[http://www12.statcan.ca/census-recensement/2006/dp-pd/hlt/97-562/pages/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo=PR&Code=01&Table=2&Data=Count&StartRec=1&Sort=3&Display=All&CSDFilter=5000 Ethnic origins, 2006 counts, for Canada, provinces and territories - 20% sample data], Statistics Canada (2006). Retrieved on August 11, 2008.</ref><ref>[http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census01/products/highlight/ETO/Table1.cfm?T=501&Lang=E&GV=1&GID=0 Ethnic Origins for Canada - 2001 Census]. Retrieved December 6th, 2013</ref><ref>[http://www.statcan.gc.ca/c1996-r1996/feb17-17fev/oe1ca-eo1ca-eng.htm Top 25 Ethnic Origins for Canada - 1996 Census]. Retrieved December 6th, 2013</ref> |region4 = United Kingdom |pop4 = 400,000+ |ref4 = <ref name="iom.int">{{cite web|url=https://www.iom.int/world-migration|title=World Migration|author=|date=15 January 2015|website=iom.int}}</ref> |region5 = [[The Bahamas]] |pop5 = 5,572<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenassauguardian.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=35308&Itemid=27|title=The Nassau Guardian Home - The Nassau Guardian|author=|date=|website=The Nassau Guardian}}</ref> |region6 = Germany |pop6 = 1,671 |ref6 = <ref name="iom.int"/> |region7 = [[Trinidad and Tobago]] |pop7 = 15,000 |ref7 = <ref name="iom.int"/> |region8 = Australia |pop8 = 1,092 |ref8 = <ref name="iom.int"/> |region9 = Other |pop9 = ~2,000–5,000 |ref9 = <ref name="iom.int"/> }}
'''Jamaicans''' are the citizens of [[Jamaica]] and their descendants in the [[Jamaican diaspora]]. Most Jamaicans are of African descent, with smaller minorities of Europeans, East Indians, Chinese and others or mixed ancestry. The bulk of the Jamaican diaspora resides in other [[Anglophone countries]], namely [[Jamaican Australians|Australia]], [[Jamaican Canadians|Canada]], [[Jamaican Americans|United States]] and the [[Jamaican British|United Kingdom]] and, to a lesser extent, other [[Caribbean Community|Caribbean countries]] and [[Commonwealth realms]].
According to the official Jamaica Population Census of 1970, ethnic origins categories in Jamaica include [[Afro-Jamaican|Black]], [[Indo-Jamaicans|East Indian]], [[Chinese Jamaicans|Chinese]], [[Lebanese Jamaicans|Syrian or Lebanese]], [[White Jamaicans|White]], mixed, and other races. Jamaicans of African or partial African descent made up 89.4% of the working population. Those of non-African mixed race were the second most prominent labour group, making up 6% of the population.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Jamaica Population Census 1970|last=|first=|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>{{Citation needed|date=March 2018}}
==Diaspora== {{Main|Jamaican diaspora}} Many Jamaicans now live overseas and outside Jamaica, while many have migrated to [[English-speaking world|Anglophone]] countries, including over 400,000 Jamaicans in the [[Jamaican British|United Kingdom]], over 300,000 [[Canada]], 800,000 in the [[United States]].
30,000 Jamaicans residing in other CARICOM member including the [[Bahamas]] (5,600),<ref name="josh">{{cite web|url=http://www.joshuaproject.net/people-profile.php|title=People Groups - Joshua Project|first=Joshua|last=Project|date=|website=www.joshuaproject.net}}</ref> [[Cuba]] (5,000),<ref name="josh"/> [[Antigua & Barbuda]], [[Barbados]] and [[Trinidad & Tobago]].<ref name="30,000 Jamaicans residing in CARICOM member states">{{cite web|url=http://www.caricomnews.net/index.php/caricom/caricom-news/regional-news/1889-skilled-jamaicans-refused-entry-into-some-caricom-states|title=30,000 Jamaicans residing in other CARICOM member states|author=|date=|website=caricomnews.net}}</ref> There are also communities of Jamaican descendants in Central America, particularly [[Costa Rica]], [[Nicaragua]], and [[Panama]].
