{{For|the Greek basketball player who participated in the national team in 1987|Panagiotis Karatzas (basketball)}}
{{Infobox person | name = Panagiotis Karatzas | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Patras]], [[Ottoman Empire]] (now [[Greece]]) | death_date = 1821 | death_place = [[Greece]] | nationality = [[Greece|Greek]] | occupation = [[Greek War of Independence|Greek revolutionary leader]] }}
'''Panagiotis Karatzas''' ({{lang-gr|Παναγιώτης Καρατζάς}}; 17th century – 1824) was a [[Greece|Greek]] revolutionary leader in [[Patras]] during the [[Greek Revolution of 1821]]. During his childhood years he showed his bravery and defiance against the [[Ottoman Empire|Turkish]] and often fighting with Turkish peers. He fled for the [[Ionian Islands]], which were then under [[United Kingdom|English]] rule, and moved to [[Zakynthos]] and enrolled into the [[British Army]] in the 3rd Greek Legion. He returned to Patras in 1809.
He was one of the main commanders during the [[Siege of Patras (1821)]]. He was against the Ottoman era local [[kodjabashis]] of the area. He was murdered by Greek rivals in 1824.
==References== *''History of the Greek Revolution'' (''Ιστορία της Ελληνικής Επανάστασης'' = ''Istoria tis Ellinikis Epanastasis''), Volumes I and II, [[Spyridon Trikoupis]], [[Nea Synora]] Publishers - [[A.A. Livani]], Athens [[1993 in literature|1993]] SET {{ISBN|960-236-370-3}}, Page 84 *''Istoria tis poleos Patron apo ton arheotaton hronon mehri tou 1921 (''Ιστορία της Πόλεως Πατρών απο των αρχαιοτάτων χρόνων μέχρι του 1921'' = ''History Of The City Of Patras From The [[Ancient Greece|Ancient Period]] Until 1921''), Volume II, [[Stefanos Thomopoulos]], Achaikes Publishers, Patras [[1999 in literature|1999]], {{ISBN|960-7960-09-2}}, Page 349 *''Peloponisii agonistes tou 1821, Nikitara apomnimonevmata'' (''Πελοποννήσιοι αγωνιστές του 1821, Νικηταρά απομνημονεύματα'' = ''Peloponnesian Revolutionary Leaders of 1821, [[Nikitaras]] Remembered''), Fotakou, Vergina Publishers, Athens [[1996 in literature|1996]] *''This article is translated and is based from the [[:el:Παναγιώτης Καρατζάς|article]] at the Greek Wikipedia ([[:el:|el:Main Page]])
