{{Use Indian English|date=September 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2013}} {{refimprove|date=March 2015}} [[File:Santhanam at Vallavanukku Pullum Aayudham Thanksgiving Meet.jpg|thumb|Santhanam at Vallavanukku Pullum Aayudham Thanksgiving Meet]]
The following is the filmography of [[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]], an Indian film actor who has predominantly appeared in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] films as a comedian. He began his career on television shows including [[STAR Vijay|Vijay TV]]'s ''[[Lollu Sabha]]'' enacting the lead role in spoofs of Tamil films. He was subsequently given a chance by actor [[Silambarasan]] in a supporting role in ''[[Manmadhan]]'' (2004) and then was signed on to appear in films including ''[[Sachien]]'' (2005) and ''[[Polladhavan (2007 film)|Polladhavan]]'' (2007). He appeared in a one-off leading role in Shankar's production ''[[Arai En 305-il Kadavul]]'' (2008) and subsequently became a staple feature as a comedian in successful Tamil films during the period, with his market popularity helping stuck films find distributors.<ref name="Santhanam the most wanted!">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-05-23/news-interviews/29573822_1_santhanam-siruthai-comedian|title=Santhanam the most wanted!|publisher=[[The Times of India]]|date=23 May 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=K. R. Manigandan |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/comedy-is-serious-business/article3314748.ece |title=Comedy is serious business |publisher=[[The Hindu]]|date=14 April 2012 |accessdate=15 November 2013}}</ref> Santhanam has also had embarked on collaborations with directors including [[M. Rajesh (director)|M. Rajesh]]'s comic trilogy of ''[[Siva Manasula Sakthi]]'' (2009), ''[[Boss Engira Bhaskaran]]'' (2010) and ''[[Oru Kal Oru Kannadi]]'' (2012).
